<h1>Exposing CraigsForce to Your Users</h1>
<p/>
Expose the app to your users via profiles.  The <i>CraigsForce User</i> custom profile has been created as an example.  Under <b>Setup | Manage Users | Profiles</b>, do the following <b>for each profile to which you would like to enable CraigsForce</b>:
	<ol>
	<li>Make the CraigsForce app visible to that profile.
	<li>Set the tab setting for the Posts custom tab to be <i>Default On</i>
	<li>Give them access to the Post custom object, specifically read, create, edit, delete, and view all:
		<br/>
		<img src="{!$Resource.postCustomObjectPref}"/>
	<li>Give them access to the following VisualForce pages:
		<br/>
		<img src="{!$Resource.cfVfAccess}"/>
</ol>
<hr/>
<h1>Scheduling a Process to Clean Up Old Posts</h1><p/>
Posts are likely to be timely, so you can schedule a process to automatically delete them after thirty days.  To do this:
<ol>
<li>Go to <b>System Log</b>.
<li>Under <b>Execute Apex</b>, copy and paste the following:
<pre>
PostingReaper.schedule();
</pre>
<li> Click <b>Execute</b>.
</ol>
